text: Nassarius cabrierensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. The subspecies Nassarius cabrierensis ovoideus (Locard, 1886) is a synonym of Nassarius ovoideus (Locard, 1886) ==Description== The shell grows to a length of 12 mm. ==Distribution== This species occurs in the Atlantic Ocean off the Western Sahara. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 1878
title: Nassarius cabrierensis
